    {
      "lineNumber": 29,
      "text": "On the afternoon of May 20, 1949, [REDACTED] of Chicago 25, Illinois, was referred to my office from the Director's Office.",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 30,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 31,
      "text": "Miss [REDACTED] stated she was going to be in Washington for a few days and that she was staying at the Ambassador Hotel. She stated that [REDACTED] of the [REDACTED] in Chicago, had some information regarding flying discs. Miss [REDACTED] said that [REDACTED] theory was to the effect that when people died their souls entered a space on this earth which is, of course, invisible to human eyes. He said that in this soul world there are good and bad people and that they have become involved in a war. According to Miss [REDACTED] theory is that the flying discs which have been seen are the explosives being used in the warfare between the good and bad souls.",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 32,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 33,
      "text": "Miss [REDACTED] stated that the real purpose of her visit to the Bureau was to get her own name cleared. She said that the FBI has been conducting investigation regarding her and that she wanted to know the results of the investigation. I asked her what kind of an investigation the FBI had been making regarding her and she stated she was under suspicion of espionage activities. I informed her that I could not furnish her with any information which is contained in the Bureau's files inasmuch as our files have been designated as confidential by the Attorney General.",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 34,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 35,
      "text": "Miss [REDACTED] accepted this explanation and stated regarding her present activities that she had been in the Wacs as a private and had received an honorable discharge in 1945. She said at the present time she is working as a model in Chicago.",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 36,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 37,
      "text": "She impressed me as being somewhat mentally unbalanced.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 38,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 39,
      "text": "A check of the files failed to reveal that we have conducted any investigation relative to this individual.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 40,
      "status": "blank"
